sentences:
William Stuart Reyburn ( December 17 , 1882 – July 25 , 1946 ) was a Republican member of the U.S. House of Representatives from Pennsylvania .
Reyburn was born in Philadelphia , Pennsylvania , to John E. Reyburn and Margretta ( Crozier ) .
He married Georgie Fontaine Maury , of Washington , June 10 , 1911 .
He graduated from Yale University in 1904 , where he was a member of St. Anthony Hall , and from the law department of Georgetown University , Washington , D.C.
He was a member of President William Howard Taft 's party that visited the Philippines , Japan , and China in 1905 .
He served in the Pennsylvania House of Representatives from 1909 until 1911 .
He was elected to 62nd Congress , May 23 , 1911 , to fill the vacancy caused by the death of Joel Cook and served from May 23 , 1911 , to March 3 , 1913 .
He declined to be a candidate for renomination in 1912 .
